             was tried for a Misdeameanor, for that he <rs id="t16931206-42-off175" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16931206-42-off175" type="offenceCategory" value="deception"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16931206-42-off175" type="offenceSubcategory" value="fraud"></interp>
               Falsly and Maliciously did pretend to have an Authority from Sir 
                     <persName id="t16931206-42-person137">
                        John 
                        Trenchard
                     <interp inst="t16931206-42-person137" type="surname" value="Trenchard"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16931206-42-person137" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16931206-42-person137" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , to dispose of certain Places, to several Persons in the Custom-house, particularly a Store-keeper's Place to one <rs id="t16931206-42-viclabel176" type="occupation">Mr.</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t16931206-42-victim138 t16931206-42-viclabel176"></join>
